entry.title: Tropical Storm Hilary Makes Landfall in Southern California
entry.content: Southern California was hit with rain, wind and even a series of earthquakes Sunday as the first tropical storm in nearly a century roared in, knocking out power, flooding streets and prompting at least one water rescue.
